creator: False
bio:
Vision:

- Convinced that a high-quality IT solution is the result of clear task definition, a deep understanding of business strategy, and formalized processes of delivering IT services.
- Confident that effective communication is a key factor in preventing misunderstandings within a team.

Experience and Skills:

- Experienced IT professional with deep expertise in various areas of information technology and product development.
- Broad perspective covering various aspects of technology and innovation.
- Active mentor in the community of architects at Sber.
- Author of articles on Habr, sharing experience and knowledge with a wide audience.
- Proven leader, achieving set goals and inspiring the team.

Professional Achievements:

- Significant experience in designing various layers of IT architecture, successfully addressing business challenges.
- Effective automation of IT production processes, optimizing workflows.
- Successful design of infrastructure architecture for corporate networks and SAN, ensuring reliability and security.
- Applied experience in configuring IT infrastructure elements (storage, servers, network equipment), ensuring efficient infrastructure operation.
- Implementation of CI/CD pipelines, ensuring continuous delivery of software.
- Deployment and integration of monitoring systems for real-time response to changes.

Interests:

- Product marketing: Creating unique strategies for successful product promotion.
- Creative pursuits: Photo and video editing, giving projects aesthetic appeal.
- AI and its multifaceted applications, including technical aspects.
- Deep knowledge of OS internals, ability to interact effectively with operating systems.
- Experience in pentesting and reverse engineering, ensuring a high level of security.
- Creation of robotic devices.
- Development of drivers and firmware for embedded systems, ensuring optimal performance and energy efficiency.
- White Hat principles.
- Preference for the Rust programming language, enriching technical expertise.

name: Ch Muhammad Awais
headline: 8x Hackathon winner | PhD Candidate in AI & Satellite Image Processing
creator: True
current_company: Institute of Information Science and Technologies
bio:
I‚Äôm currently pursuing a PhD in Computer Science at the University of Pisa, diving deep into satellite image analysis and SAR ship classification to tackle challenges in maritime monitoring. At CNR-ISTI, I apply machine learning to environmental sustainability projects, working on ship detection, speed estimation, and oil spill analysis using cutting-edge deep learning models.

Previously, I‚Äôve developed data-driven solutions as a Data Science Specialist at Tatneft and optimized OCR systems as a Junior Software Developer at MicroMerger. My hands-on experience spans AI-powered tools, hackathon-winning projects, and applications in computer vision, NLP, and MLOps. With expertise in PyTorch, TensorFlow, GCP, and PowerBI, I thrive in building innovative systems that solve real-world problems.

Fluent in English, Russian, and Italian, I enjoy collaborating with global teams to create impactful AI solutions, especially those advancing sustainability and environmental protection.

name: Aleksei Ratiner
headline: Operations \ Project \ Supply manager
creator: False
bio:
Senior manager with 15 years of experience in retail enterprises with matrix management structure. Successful experience of the projects realization in cross-functional teams: new store openings, sales, e-commerce, food production, logistics, marketing, HR, cost saving management.

I‚Äôm helping organizations to increase sales and develop management system, implement sales and profit development projects, train employees and talent develop. I'd like to apply my experience in the new industry and develop further in IT to improve operational efficiency and business profitability of the company.

SOFT SKILLS
‚Ä¢	System thinking, focus on the result, focus on details
‚Ä¢	Leadership, communications management, managing of remote and cross-functional teams
‚Ä¢	Project management, innovation approaches, commercial wide view
‚Ä¢	Customer oriented

HARD SKILLS
‚Ä¢	Operational management by KPI and OKR; retail sales and wholesales development; market research and sales model adaptation; e-commerce
‚Ä¢	Commercial and marketing management: new suppliers, traffic attraction, big data analysis and customer research studies, CJM, customer service
‚Ä¢	Negotiations and communications: suppliers, contractors, stakeholders. Suppliers due diligence.
‚Ä¢	Improving operational efficiency: organizational transformation; cost optimization, business process
optimization, staff planning
‚Ä¢	Operational and strategic financial management: audit, budgeting, analytics, P&L, Cash Flow
‚Ä¢	Project management from idea generation to implementation by Waterfall and Agile approaches,
launching new products
‚Ä¢	Team management of distributed, cross-functional and remote teams up to 20 managers in up to 10
locations with more than 1500 employees in total
‚Ä¢	People management: recruitment, evaluation, talent development, mentoring and training, retention
